2007-05-01  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	UObject::send can be used in remote or plugged mode to send commands
	to URBI. In plugged mode, the commands are immediately executed.

	add support of UObject::send
	* urbi/fwd.hh: define UGhostConnection for plugged UObjects.
	* urbi/uobject.hh.template: add gc and send in UObject.

2007-05-01  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	This method is called by a UVariable destructor for every UVar that
	points to the destructed UVariable, effectively making the UVar
	ineffective. It's just a first step in what should be done: proper
	messages should be sent on the UObject side to let the user know that
	something bad has just happened.

	At least, the server does not crash anymore and that's the minimum we
	can do for our users.

	See subsequent commits for remote implementation of uvar.cc.

	add a setZombie method to UVar.
	* urbi/uvar.hh: add setZombie.

